other_tests.findings: Ventricular rate of 51 beats per minute and was otherwise normal.
Minimal disease of the left internal carotid artery and of the right carotid artery at the bifurcation.
Opening pressure of 14 cm of water, clear cerebrospinal fluid, glucose level of 64 mg/dL, protein level of 65 mg/dL, and cell count with minimal white cells.
Continuous focal slowing in the right hemisphere, mostly in the anterior region. No epileptiform activity present.
No abnormalities in the measurement of porphobilinogen and aminolevulinic acid.
